  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Implicit Copy On Return (ReturnTypeImplicitCopy)"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Returning ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Array",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Dictionary",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " values from functions and closures is a common",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "pattern in Swift. However, these collection types are backed by heap-allocated",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "storage, and returning them from a function produces an implicit copy of the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "collection value.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Problem",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Problem",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When a function returns an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Array",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Dictionary",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", it must first construct",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the collection in heap-allocated backing storage. The caller then receives a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "copy of the collection value - a wrapper struct that contains a pointer to that",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "storage. Although no element-by-element deep copy occurs at the return boundary",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "(Swift’s collections use copy-on-write to defer that until mutation), the heap",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "allocation itself is unavoidable, and the copy of the wrapper value carries its",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "own costs.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Heap Allocation",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "strong"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ": The called function must heap-allocate backing storage",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "for the collection it constructs. This allocation cost is paid on every call,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "and the storage is deallocated once the ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "caller",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is done with the result.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Reference Counting",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "strong"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ": The backing storage is reference-counted. Passing",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "the wrapper value to the caller involves retain\/release operations, and when",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "the caller’s copy goes out of scope, the storage must be released and",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "potentially deallocated.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "These costs are especially significant in performance-critical ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "loops",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", where",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "calling a function that returns a collection on every iteration leads to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "repeated allocations and reference counting overhead that can dominate execution",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "time. The compiler is often unable to eliminate these costs because the returned",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "collection may be mutated or escape in ways that prevent the optimizer from",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "proving the copy is unnecessary.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ Each call allocates and returns a new array",
            "func getVisibleItems() -> [Item] {",
            "  \/\/ ... computes and returns a collection of items",
            "}",
            "",
            "\/\/ In a performance-critical loop, the costs of this operation are incurred on",
            "\/\/ every iteration.",
            "for frame in frames {",
            "  let items = getVisibleItems() \/\/ allocation + copy on each iteration",
            "  render(items)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Alternatives",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Alternatives",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "1-Use-inout-parameters",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "1. Use `inout` parameters",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Pass the collection as an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "inout",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameter instead of returning it. This allows",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the function to populate the caller’s collection directly, avoiding the need to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "allocate and return a new value.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "func getVisibleItems(_ result: inout [Item]) {",
            "  \/\/ ... appends into the caller's collection",
            "}",
            "",
            "var items: [Item] = []",
            "getVisibleItems(&items)"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When used in a loop, the caller can reuse the same collection across iterations",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "by clearing and refilling it, avoiding the need for repeated heap allocations",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "entirely.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "var items: [Item] = []",
            "for frame in frames {",
            "  items.removeAll(keepingCapacity: true)",
            "  getVisibleItems(&items)",
            "  render(items)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "2-Use-Span-for-read-only-access",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "2. Use `Span` for read-only access",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When the caller only needs to read the collection’s elements without taking",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "ownership, consider exposing the data as a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/span",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". A ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Span",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "non-escapable view into contiguous memory. The compiler guarantees that a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Span",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "cannot outlive the view data so its usage incurs no additional heap allocation",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and reference counting overhead. The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Span",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " value itself is a lightweight data",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "structure with a pointer and a count, making it cheap to create and pass around.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This approach works well when the data the function is returning is already",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "stored somewhere with a known lifetime. Instead of returning a copy of the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "collection, expose a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Span",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " that presents a view of the existing storage:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "struct Scene {",
            "  var visibleItems: [Item]",
            "  var visibleItemSpan: Span<Item> {",
            "    self.visibleItems.span",
            "  }",
            "}",
            "",
            "for frame in frames {",
            "  let items = scene.visibleItemSpan \/\/ no allocation, no copy",
            "  render(items)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "3-Restructure-to-avoid-returning-transient-collections",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "3. Restructure to avoid returning transient collections",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In some cases, a function builds a collection only for the caller to immediately",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "process and discard it. The collection itself is transient so the caller does",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "not need to own a standalone copy of it. This pattern can be restructured so",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that the function passes the data to a caller-provided closure instead of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "returning it, avoiding the allocation entirely.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example, consider a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "pop",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " operation on a stack type, which would naturally",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "return an array:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ Allocates a new array on every call",
            "mutating func pop(count: Int) -> [Element] {",
            "  let result = Array(items.suffix(count))",
            "  items.removeLast(count)",
            "  return result",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Instead, the function can grant the caller temporary read-only access to the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "elements via a closure, then remove them afterward. No intermediate collection",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "is allocated:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ Passes a view of the popped elements to the closure, then removes them",
            "mutating func pop<T>(",
            "  count: Int,",
            "  _ body: (borrowing Span<Element>) -> T",
            ") -> T {",
            "  defer { items.removeLast(count) }",
            "  return body(items.span.extracting(last: count))",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The caller processes the elements through the closure without ever owning a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "separate collection:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "stack.pop(count: n) { elements in",
            "  for i in elements.indices {",
            "    process(elements[i])",
            "  }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Summary",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Summary",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Returning ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Array",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Dictionary",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " values from functions involves heap allocation",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and reference counting overhead that can accumulate in performance-critical code",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "paths. Use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "inout",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameters to allow the caller to provide and reuse storage,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Span",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for non-owning read-only access, or restructure the code to avoid",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "materializing intermediate collections. These alternatives eliminate the implicit",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "copies that occur when returning collection values.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
